To prove the Marcinkiewicz-Zygmund inequality for symmetric random variables in Lean 4, we need to show that if $X_1, \ldots, X_n$ are independent symmetric random variables taking values in an inner product space $E$ over $\mathbb{R}$, then:

$$\mathbb{E}\left[\| \sum_{i=1}^n X_i \|^p\right] \leq C_p \cdot \mathbb{E}\left[ \left( \sum_{i=1}^n \|X_i\|^2 \right)^{p/2} \right]$$

